-- Colombian Stock Movers: Avianca Taca, Colinveriones Advance
-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 2012-01-19T21:39:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-19/colombian-stock-movers-avianca-taca-colinveriones-advance.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. local time.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  gained 0.1 percent to 13,476.59, while the
Colcap Index fell 0.4 percent to 1,606.49.  Avianca Taca Holding SA (PFAVTA)  (PFAVTA CB), the owner of
 Colombia ’s largest airline, rose 7.2 percent, the most since the
stock began trading on May 11, to 3,700 pesos.  The company gained as investors bet the it is undervalued
after shares fell 32 percent in the fourth quarter of 2011, said
 Andres Jimenez , head of international sales at Interbolsa SA,
Colombia’s biggest brokerage.  Cia. Colombiana de Inversiones SA  (COLINV CB), a Colombian
electricity holding company, advanced 3.1 percent to 4,350
pesos. The shares have gained 14 percent this year as investors
bet the company will seek to use accumulated cash on hand for an
expansion, possibly by participating in public bids this year
for electricity generation projects, said Jairo Agudelo, an
analyst at Celfin Capital.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blake Schmidt in Bogota at 
